text:
Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into
garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw,
rotting trash.

name: Weezing
attack: [{"info": "{DD} Smokescreen 50", "effect": "During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pok\u00e9mon tries to use an attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen."}]
text:
If one of the twin Koffing inflates, the other one
deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.

name: Purrloin
attack: [{"info": "{D} Scratch 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It steals things from people just to amuse itself
with their frustration. A rivalry exists between
this Pokémon and Nickit.

name: Liepard
attack: [{"info": "{D} Slash 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
Don’t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant
figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

name: Venipede
attack: [{"info": "{D} Ram 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
Venipede and Sizzlipede are similar species,
but when the two meet, a huge fight ensues.

name: Whirlipede
attack: [{"info": "{D} Poison Sting 20", "effect": "Your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Poisoned."}]
text:
This Pokémon spins itself rapidly and charges into
its opponents. Its top speed is just over 60 mph.

name: Scolipede
attack: [{"info": "{DC} Venoshock 70+", "effect": "If your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is Poisoned, this attack does 50 more damage."}]
text:
Scolipede latches on to its prey with the claws on
its neck before slamming them into the ground
and jabbing them with its claws’ toxic spikes.

name: Druddigon
attack: [{"info": "{RWC} Dragon Claw 90", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Rough Skin", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent\u2019s Pok\u00e9mon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Druddigon lives in caves, but it never skips
sunbathing—it won’t be able to move if its body
gets too cold.

name: Pidgey
attack: [{"info": "{C} Flap 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps
its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

name: Pidgeotto
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Wing Attack 50", "effect": ""}]
text:
The claws on its feet are well developed.
It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute
to its nest over 60 miles away.

name: Pidgeot ex
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Scattering Cyclone 80+", "effect": "This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Tauros
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Fighting Tackle 40+", "effect": "If your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is a Pok\u00e9mon ex, this attack does 80 more damage."}]
text:
When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails,
it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to
charge with astounding speed.

name: Eevee
attack: [{"info": "{C} Continuous Steps 20x", "effect": "Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads."}]
text:
Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to
adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Chatot
attack: [{"info": "{C} Mimic", "effect": "Shuffle your hand into your deck. Draw a card for each card in your opponent's hand."}]
text:
It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them
into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t
attack it.

name: Old Amber
text:
Play this card as if it were a 40-HP Basic {C} Pokémon.
At any time during your turn, you may discard this card from play.
This card can't retreat.

name: Pokémon Flute
rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Mythical Slab
rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Budding Expeditioner
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Blue
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Leaf
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Exeggutor
attack: [{"info": "{GCCC} Psychic 80+", "effect": "This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking
different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be
very interested in one another.

name: Serperior
attack: [{"info": "{GCCC} Solar Beam 70", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Jungle Totem", "effect": "Each Energy attached to your Pok\u00e9mon provides 2 Energy. This effect doesn\u2019t stack."}]
text:
It only gives its all against strong opponents who
are not fazed by the glare from Serperior’s
noble eyes.

name: Salandit
attack: [{"info": "{C} Venoshock 10+", "effect": "If your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is Poisoned, this attack does 40 more damage."}]
text:
It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow,
rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic
gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

name: Vaporeon
attack: [{"info": "{WCC} Wave Splash 60", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Wash Out", "effect": "As often as you like during your turn, you may move a Energy from 1 of your Benched Pok\u00e9mon to your Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with
a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

name: Dedenne
attack: [{"info": "{L} Thunder Shock 10", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Paralyzed."}]
text:
It’s small and its electricity-generating organ is
not fully developed, so it uses its tail to absorb
electricity from people’s homes and charge itself.

name: Marshadow
attack: [{"info": "{FC} Revenge 40+", "effect": "If any of your Pok\u00e9mon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 60 more damage."}]
text:
It slips into the shadows of others and mimics
their powers and movements. As it improves, it
becomes stronger than those it’s imitating.

name: Celebi ex
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Powerful Bloom 50x", "effect": "Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pok\u00e9mon. This attack does 50 damage for each heads."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Gyarados ex
attack: [{"info": "{WWWC} Rampaging Whirlpool 140", "effect": "Discard a random Energy from among the Energy attached to all Pok\u00e9mon (both yours and your opponent's)."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Mew ex
attack: [{"info": "{P} Psyshot 20", "effect": ""}, {"info": "{CCC} Genome Hacking", "effect": "Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon's attacks and use it as this attack."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Aerodactyl ex
attack: [{"info": "{FC} Land Crush 80", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Primeval Law", "effect": "Your opponent can\u2019t play any Pok\u00e9mon from their hand to evolve their Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Pidgeot ex
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Scattering Cyclone 80+", "effect": "This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Budding Expeditioner
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Blue
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Leaf
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Mew ex
attack: [{"info": "{P} Psyshot 20", "effect": ""}, {"info": "{CCC} Genome Hacking", "effect": "Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon's attacks and use it as this attack."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Aerodactyl ex
attack: [{"info": "{FC} Land Crush 80", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Primeval Law", "effect": "Your opponent can\u2019t play any Pok\u00e9mon from their hand to evolve their Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Celebi ex
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Powerful Bloom 50x", "effect": "Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pok\u00e9mon. This attack does 50 damage for each heads."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Mew ex
attack: [{"info": "{P} Psyshot 20", "effect": ""}, {"info": "{CCC} Genome Hacking", "effect": "Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon's attacks and use it as this attack."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Old Amber
rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Oddish
attack: [{"info": "{G} Blot 10", "effect": "Heal 10 damage from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move.
It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

name: Gloom
attack: [{"info": "{G} Razor Leaf 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor.
The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance
of 1.25 miles.

name: Tangela
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Vine Whip 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows
nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this
Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

name: Tangrowth
attack: [{"info": "{GGGC} Mega Drain 90", "effect": "Heal 30 damage from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it
pleases. Recent research has shown that these
arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

name: Yanma
attack: [{"info": "{C} Flap 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its
head. It won’t miss prey—even those behind it.

name: Yanmega ex
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Air Slash 120", "effect": "Discard a random Energy from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Roselia
attack: [{"info": "{G} Sting 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance.
The stronger its aroma, the healthier
the Roselia is.

name: Roserade
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Poisonous Whip 50", "effect": "Your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Poisoned."}]
text:
After captivating opponents with its sweet scent,
it lashes them with its thorny whips.

name: Burmy
attack: [{"info": "{C} Tackle 10", "effect": ""}]
text:
To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers
itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: Combee
attack: [{"info": "{C} Call for Family", "effect": "Put 1 random Basic Pok\u00e9mon from your deck onto your Bench."}]
text:
At night, Combee sleep in a group of about a
hundred, packed closely together in a lump.

name: Vespiquen
attack: [{"info": "{GG} Pierce 70", "effect": ""}]
text:
It houses its colony in cells in its body and
releases various pheromones to make those
grubs do its bidding.

name: Leafeon
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Leafy Cyclone 90", "effect": "During your next turn, this Pok\u00e9mon can't attack."}]
text:
When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of
sunshine, you’ll know it is using photosynthesis
to produce clean air.

name: Mow Rotom
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Energy Cutoff 30", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
The lawn mower is one of the household
appliances that led to the development of
the Rotom Dex.

name: Shaymin
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Flop 30", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Fragrant Flower Garden", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may heal 10 damage from each of your Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly
transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

name: Slugma
attack: [{"info": "{R} Flare 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers
around in a constant search for warm places.

name: Heat Rotom
attack: [{"info": "{RC} Heat Breath 30+", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage."}]
text:
If the convection microwave oven is not working
properly, then the Rotom inhabiting it will
become lethargic.

name: Swinub
attack: [{"info": "{WC} Headbutt 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up
food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

name: Piloswine
attack: [{"info": "{WWC} Hammer In 60", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Thick Fat", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon takes \u221220 damage from attacks from or Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back
stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

name: Mamoswine
attack: [{"info": "{WWCC} Frosty Flattening 120", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Thick Fat", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon takes \u221230 damage from attacks from or Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
This Pokémon can be spotted in wall paintings
from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a
while, it was thought to have gone extinct.

name: Floatzel
attack: [{"info": "{W} Jet Screw 30+", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage."}]
text:
With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people
on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

name: Finneon
attack: [{"info": "{W} Elegant Swim 10", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from\u2014and effects of\u2014attacks done to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
The line running down its side can store sunlight.
It shines vividly at night.

name: Lumineon
attack: [{"info": "{W} Waterfall 50", "effect": ""}]
text:
With its shining light, it lures its prey close.
However, the light also happens to attract
ferocious fish Pokémon—its natural predators.

name: Snover
attack: [{"info": "{W} Ice Shard 10+", "effect": "If your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is a {F} Pok\u00e9mon, this attack does 30 more damage."}]
text:
During cold seasons, it migrates to the
mountain’s lower reaches. It returns to the
snow-covered summit in the spring.

name: Abomasnow
attack: [{"info": "{WWWC} Frost Breath 120", "effect": ""}]
text:
It lives a quiet life on mountains that are
perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself
by whipping up blizzards.

name: Wash Rotom
attack: [{"info": "{W} Wave Splash 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
This Rotom has entered a washing machine.
It nods with satisfaction after it floods the
surrounding area.

name: Frost Rotom
attack: [{"info": "{WW} Blizzard 30", "effect": "This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
This Rotom has entered a refrigerator. It leaps
around gleefully after it uses cold air to freeze
the area around it.

name: Magnemite
attack: [{"info": "{C} Ram 10", "effect": ""}]
text:
The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units
at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which
allows it to float.

name: Magneton
attack: [{"info": "{LL} Lightning Ball 50", "effect": ""}]
text:
Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic
force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

name: Magnezone
attack: [{"info": "{LCC} Thunder Blast 110", "effect": "Discard a {L} Energy from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems
to be receiving signals of unknown origin while
transmitting signals of unknown purpose.

name: Electrode
attack: [{"info": "{L} Rolling Attack 50", "effect": ""}]
text:
The more energy it charges up, the faster
it gets. But this also makes it more likely
to explode.

name: Electabuzz
attack: [{"info": "{L} Charge", "effect": "Take a {L} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon
around as a defense against Electabuzz that
come seeking electricity.

name: Electivire
attack: [{"info": "{LL} Exciting Voltage 40+", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon has at least 2 extra {L} Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage."}]
text:
The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon
produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse.
The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.

name: Shinx
attack: [{"info": "{L} Hide", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from\u2014and effects of\u2014attacks done to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
The extension and contraction of its muscles
generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

name: Luxio
attack: [{"info": "{LC} Electric Claws 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
Strong electricity courses through the tips of
its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting
in foes.

name: Luxray
attack: [{"info": "{LLL} Volt Bolt", "effect": "Discard all {L} Energy from this Pok\u00e9mon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It can see clearly through walls to track down its
prey and seek its lost young.

name: Pachirisu ex
attack: [{"info": "{LL} Sparking Gadget 40+", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon has a Pok\u00e9mon Tool attached, this attack does 40 more damage."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Togepi
attack: [{"info": "{P} Pound 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said
that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

name: Togekiss
attack: [{"info": "{PP} Overdrive Smash 60", "effect": "During your next turn, this Pok\u00e9mon's Overdrive Smash attack does +60 damage."}]
text:
These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near
conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they’ve hardly
been seen at all.

name: Ralts
attack: [{"info": "{C} Teleport", "effect": "Switch this Pok\u00e9mon with 1 of your Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
The horns on its head provide a strong power
that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

name: Kirlia
attack: [{"info": "{C} Slap 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It has a psychic power that enables it to distort
the space around it and see into the future.

name: Duskull
attack: [{"info": "{P} Will-O-Wisp 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
If it finds bad children who won’t listen to their
parents, it will spirit them away—or so it’s said.

name: Dusclops
attack: [{"info": "{PCC} Psypunch 50", "effect": ""}]
text:
It seeks drifting will-o’-the-wisps and sucks them
into its empty body. What happens inside is
a mystery.

name: Dusknoir
attack: [{"info": "{PCC} Devour Soul 70", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Shadow Void", "effect": "As often as you like during your turn, you may choose 1 of your Pok\u00e9mon that has damage on it, and move all of its damage to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit
world, it steals people and Pokémon away.
No one knows whether it has a will of its own.

name: Drifloon
attack: [{"info": "{P} Expand 10", "effect": "During your opponent's next turn, this Pok\u00e9mon takes \u221220 damage from attacks."}]
text:
It is whispered that any child who mistakes
Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could
wind up missing.

name: Drifblim
attack: [{"info": "{PP} Balloon Strike 60", "effect": ""}]
text:
Some say this Pokémon is a collection of souls
burdened with regrets, silently drifting through
the dusk.

name: Gligar
attack: [{"info": "{F} Pierce 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey,
it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.

name: Gliscor
attack: [{"info": "{F} Acrobatics 20+", "effect": "Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads."}]
text:
It observes prey while hanging inverted from
branches. When the chance presents itself,
it swoops!

name: Hitmontop
attack: [{"info": "{FF} Spinning Attack 50", "effect": ""}]
text:
It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high
speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

name: Nosepass
attack: [{"info": "{CC} Ram 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
It moves less than an inch a year, but when
it’s in a jam, it will spin and drill down into the
ground in a split second.

name: Cranidos
attack: [{"info": "{F} Headbutt 50", "effect": ""}]
text:
A primeval Pokémon, it possesses a hard and
sturdy skull, lacking any intelligence within.

name: Rampardos
attack: [{"info": "{F} Head Smash 130", "effect": "If your opponent's Pok\u00e9mon is Knocked Out by damage from this attack, this Pok\u00e9mon also does 50 damage to itself."}]
text:
In ancient times, people would dig up fossils of
this Pokémon and use its skull, which is harder
than steel, to make helmets.

name: Wormadam
attack: [{"info": "{FCC} Land Crush 70", "effect": ""}]
text:
Its appearance changes depending on where it
evolved. The materials on hand become a part of
its body.

name: Riolu
attack: [{"info": "{F} Jab 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
They communicate with one another using their
auras. They are able to run all through the night.

name: Lucario
attack: [{"info": "{FF} Submarine Blow 40", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Fighting Coach", "effect": "Attacks used by your Pok\u00e9mon do +20 damage to your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It’s said that no foe can remain invisible to
Lucario, since it can detect auras—even those
of foes it could not otherwise see.

name: Gallade ex
attack: [{"info": "{FF} Energized Blade 70+", "effect": "This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Murkrow
attack: [{"info": "{D} Peck 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to
bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

name: Honchkrow
attack: [{"info": "{DD} Skill Dive", "effect": "This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never
forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.

name: Mightyena
attack: [{"info": "{DC} Darkness Fang 60", "effect": ""}]
text:
It will always obey the commands of a skilled
Trainer. Its behavior arises from its living in packs
in ancient times.

name: Stunky
attack: [{"info": "{D} Scratch 10", "effect": ""}]
text:
It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench
spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon
away.

name: Skuntank
attack: [{"info": "{DC} Poison Gas 50", "effect": "Your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Poisoned."}]
text:
It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from
the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.

name: Skorupi
attack: [{"info": "{DC} Pierce 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
After burrowing into the sand, it waits patiently
for prey to come near. This Pokémon and
Sizzlipede share common descent.

name: Croagunk
attack: [{"info": "{DD} Group Beatdown 20x", "effect": "Flip a coin for each Pok\u00e9mon you have in play. This attack does 20 damage for each heads."}]
text:
Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an
odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a
poison jab.

name: Toxicroak
attack: [{"info": "{DD} Group Beatdown 40x", "effect": "Flip a coin for each Pok\u00e9mon you have in play. This attack does 40 damage for each heads."}]
text:
Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes, it
weaves its flexible body in close, then lunges
out with its poisonous claws.

name: Darkrai
attack: [{"info": "{DDC} Dark Void 60", "effect": "Your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Asleep."}]
text:
It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by
causing them to experience deep,
nightmarish slumbers.

name: Darkrai ex
attack: [{"info": "{DDC} Dark Prism 80", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Nightmare Aura", "effect": "Whenever you attach a Energy from your Energy Zone to this Pok\u00e9mon, do 20 damage to your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Registeel
attack: [{"info": "{MMM} Metal Claw 90", "effect": ""}]
text:
Registeel’s body is made of a strange material
that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but
also more durable than any metal.

name: Bronzor
attack: [{"info": "{MC} Tackle 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
Ancient people believed that the pattern on
Bronzor’s back contained a mysterious power.

name: Bronzong
attack: [{"info": "{MMC} Guard Press 60", "effect": "During your opponent's next turn, this Pok\u00e9mon takes \u221220 damage from attacks."}]
text:
In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a
bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

name: Dialga ex
attack: [{"info": "{MM} Metallic Turbo 30", "effect": "Take 2 {M} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}, {"info": "{MMCC} Heavy Impact 100", "effect": ""}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Heatran
attack: [{"info": "{MMM} Steel Tackle 110", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon also does 20 damage to itself."}]
text:
It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its
cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Eevee
attack: [{"info": "{C} Quick Attack 10+", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage."}]
text:
Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to
adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Aipom
attack: [{"info": "{C} Tail Jab 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
As it did more and more with its tail, its hands
became clumsy. It makes its nest high in
the treetops.

name: Bidoof
attack: [{"info": "{CC} Super Fang", "effect": "Halve your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon's remaining HP, rounded down."}]
text:
With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is
more agile and active than it appears.

name: Bibarel
attack: [{"info": "{CC} Rolling Tackle 60", "effect": ""}]
text:
It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and
roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.

name: Buneary
attack: [{"info": "{C} Splash 10", "effect": ""}]
text:
If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up, something
is wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign the
Pokémon is in need of care.

name: Lopunny
attack: [{"info": "{C} Jump Kick 20", "effect": "This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings.
If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds
with superdestructive kicks.

name: Fan Rotom
attack: [{"info": "{CC} Spin Storm", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, put your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon into their hand."}]
text:
This Rotom has entered an electric fan. It smirks
with satisfaction over a prank well pulled after it
blows away everything around it.

rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

attack: [{"info": "{GGGC} Mega Drain 90", "effect": "Heal 30 damage from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it
pleases. Recent research has shown that these
arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

name: Combee
attack: [{"info": "{C} Call for Family", "effect": "Put 1 random Basic Pok\u00e9mon from your deck onto your Bench."}]
text:
At night, Combee sleep in a group of about a
hundred, packed closely together in a lump.

name: Shaymin
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Flop 30", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Fragrant Flower Garden", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may heal 10 damage from each of your Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly
transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

name: Mamoswine
attack: [{"info": "{WWCC} Frosty Flattening 120", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Thick Fat", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon takes \u221230 damage from attacks from or Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
This Pokémon can be spotted in wall paintings
from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a
while, it was thought to have gone extinct.

name: Shinx
attack: [{"info": "{L} Hide", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from\u2014and effects of\u2014attacks done to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
The extension and contraction of its muscles
generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

name: Drifloon
attack: [{"info": "{P} Expand 10", "effect": "During your opponent's next turn, this Pok\u00e9mon takes \u221220 damage from attacks."}]
text:
It is whispered that any child who mistakes
Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could
wind up missing.

name: Mesprit
attack: [{"info": "{PPP} Supreme Blast 160", "effect": "You can use this attack only if you have Uxie and Azelf on your Bench. Discard all Energy from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught
humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: Lucario
attack: [{"info": "{FF} Submarine Blow 40", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Fighting Coach", "effect": "Attacks used by your Pok\u00e9mon do +20 damage to your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It’s said that no foe can remain invisible to
Lucario, since it can detect auras—even those
of foes it could not otherwise see.

name: Croagunk
attack: [{"info": "{DD} Group Beatdown 20x", "effect": "Flip a coin for each Pok\u00e9mon you have in play. This attack does 20 damage for each heads."}]
text:
Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an
odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a
poison jab.

name: Heatran
attack: [{"info": "{MMM} Steel Tackle 110", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon also does 20 damage to itself."}]
text:
It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its
cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Bidoof
attack: [{"info": "{CC} Super Fang", "effect": "Halve your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon's remaining HP, rounded down."}]
text:
With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is
more agile and active than it appears.

name: Regigigas
attack: [{"info": "{CCCC} Raging Hammer 50+", "effect": "This attack does more damage equal to the damage this Pok\u00e9mon has on it."}]
text:
It is said to have made Pokémon that look like
itself from a special ice mountain, rocks,
and magma.

rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Bellossom
attack: [{"info": "{GG} Leaf Step 80", "effect": ""}]
text:
Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals
rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

name: Turtwig
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Bite 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
It uses its whole body to photosynthesize when
exposed to sunlight. Its shell is made from
hardened soil.

name: Grotle
attack: [{"info": "{GGC} Razor Leaf 60", "effect": ""}]
text:
It lives along water in forests. In the daytime,
it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

name: Torterra
attack: [{"info": "{GGCC} Frenzy Plant 150", "effect": "During your next turn, this Pok\u00e9mon can't use Frenzy Plant."}]
text:
Ancient people imagined that beneath the
ground dwelt a gigantic Torterra.

name: Kricketot
attack: [{"info": "{G} Bug Bite 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff
antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.

name: Kricketune
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Entrancing Melody 50", "effect": "Your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Confused."}]
text:
By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its
belly, it produces a captivating sound.

name: Wormadam
attack: [{"info": "{GCC} Leaf Cutter 60+", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage."}]
text:
Its appearance changes depending on where it
evolved. The materials on hand become a part of
its body.

name: Carnivine
attack: [{"info": "{GGC} Flog 40+", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage."}]
text:
It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then
chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

name: Magmar
attack: [{"info": "{R} Stoke", "effect": "Take a {R} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it
regrets this habit once it realizes that it has
burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

name: Magmortar
attack: [{"info": "{RRRR} Bursting Inferno 100", "effect": "Your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Burned."}]
text:
When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning
in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to
over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Magcargo
attack: [{"info": "{RC} Searing Flame 30", "effect": "Your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Burned."}]
text:
Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames
that circulate throughout its body.

name: Chimchar
attack: [{"info": "{R} Scratch 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly.
Even rain can’t extinguish the fire.

name: Monferno
attack: [{"info": "{R} Fiery Punch 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its
tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

name: Infernape ex
attack: [{"info": "{RR} Flare Blitz 140", "effect": "Discard all {R} Energy from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Regice
attack: [{"info": "{WW} Frost Smash 50", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Crystal Body", "effect": "Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent\u2019s Pok\u00e9mon done to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
With cold air that can reach temperatures as low
as −328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly
freezes any creature that approaches it.

name: Piplup
attack: [{"info": "{C} Nap", "effect": "Heal 20 damage from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It doesn’t like to be taken care of. It’s difficult to
bond with since it won’t listen to its Trainer.

name: Prinplup
attack: [{"info": "{WC} Surf 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every
one of them believes it is the most important.

name: Empoleon
attack: [{"info": "{WWC} Aqua Jet 80", "effect": "This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its
wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.

name: Buizel
attack: [{"info": "{W} Water Gun 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself
through water. The tails also slice clinging
seaweed.

name: Shellos
attack: [{"info": "{WC} Mud-Slap 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
It used to have a shell on its back long ago.
This species is closely related to Pokémon
like Shellder.

name: Gastrodon
attack: [{"info": "{WCC} Muddy Water 60", "effect": "This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
They normally inhabit rocky seashores, but in
times of continuous rain, they can sometimes be
found in the mountains, far from the sea.

name: Glaceon
attack: [{"info": "{WW} Ice Beam 60", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Paralyzed."}]
text:
It can control its body temperature at will.
This enables it to freeze the moisture in the
atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.

name: Palkia ex
attack: [{"info": "{W} Slash 30", "effect": ""}, {"info": "{WWWC} Dimensional Storm 150", "effect": "Discard 3 {W} Energy from this Pok\u00e9mon. This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Manaphy
attack: [{"info": "{W} Oceanic Gift", "effect": "Choose 2 of your Benched Pok\u00e9mon. For each of those Pok\u00e9mon, take a {W} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to that Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond
with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Voltorb
attack: [{"info": "{L} Big Explosion 30", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon also does 10 damage to itself."}]
text:
It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden
jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Rotom
attack: [{"info": "{C} Assault Laser 20+", "effect": "If your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon has a Pok\u00e9mon Tool attached, this attack does 30 more damage."}]
text:
Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds
of machines and take control in order to make
mischief.

name: Togetic
attack: [{"info": "{P} Fairy Wind 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
They say that it will appear before kindhearted,
caring people and shower them with happiness.

name: Misdreavus
attack: [{"info": "{P} Mumble 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
This Pokémon startles people in the middle of
the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

name: Mismagius ex
attack: [{"info": "{PP} Magical Delusion 70", "effect": "Your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Confused."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Uxie
attack: [{"info": "{P} Mind Boost 20", "effect": "Take a {P} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to Mesprit or Azelf."}]
text:
Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said
that it can wipe out the memory of those who see
its eyes.

name: Mesprit
attack: [{"info": "{PPP} Supreme Blast 160", "effect": "You can use this attack only if you have Uxie and Azelf on your Bench. Discard all Energy from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught
humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: Azelf
attack: [{"info": "{P} Psychic Arrow", "effect": "This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the
bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

name: Giratina
attack: [{"info": "{PPC} Spooky Shot 70", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Levitate", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost."}]
text:
This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the
reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is
distorted and strange.

name: Cresselia
attack: [{"info": "{PP} Moonlight Gain 50", "effect": "Heal 20 damage from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Shiny particles are released from its wings like a
veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Rhyhorn
attack: [{"info": "{FC} Horn Attack 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can
shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

name: Rhydon
attack: [{"info": "{FFC} Wrack Down 70", "effect": ""}]
text:
It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution.
It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

name: Rhyperior
attack: [{"info": "{FFFC} Mountain Swing 150", "effect": "Discard the top 3 cards of your deck."}]
text:
It can load up to three projectiles per arm into
the holes in its hands. What launches out of those
holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.

name: Regirock
attack: [{"info": "{FFFC} Boulder Crush 100", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Exoskeleton", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon takes \u221220 damage from attacks."}]
text:
Every bit of Regirock’s body is made of stone.
As parts of its body erode, this Pokémon sticks
rocks to itself to repair what’s been lost.

name: Hippopotas
attack: [{"info": "{FFC} Rolling Tackle 60", "effect": ""}]
text:
It shuts its nostrils tight, then travels through sand
as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.

name: Hippowdon
attack: [{"info": "{FFFC} Earthen Press 120", "effect": ""}]
text:
It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth
agape as a display of its strength.

name: Sneasel
attack: [{"info": "{D} Double Scratch 20x", "effect": "Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads."}]
text:
This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of
darkness, waiting to attack its prey.

name: Weavile ex
attack: [{"info": "{D} Scratching Nails 30+", "effect": "If your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon has damage on it, this attack does 40 more damage."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Poochyena
attack: [{"info": "{D} Bite 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its
chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

name: Spiritomb
attack: [{"info": "{C} Swirling Disaster", "effect": "This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted
in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a
mysterious spell.

name: Drapion
attack: [{"info": "{DDD} Cross Poison 40x", "effect": "Flip 4 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads. If at least 2 of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Poisoned."}]
text:
Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This
Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead,
going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

name: Skarmory
attack: [{"info": "{M} Metal Arms 20+", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon has a Pok\u00e9mon Tool attached, this attack does 30 more damage."}]
text:
People fashion swords from Skarmory’s shed
feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element
in heraldic designs.

name: Shieldon
attack: [{"info": "{MC} Headbutt 50", "effect": ""}]
text:
A mild-mannered, herbivorous Pokémon, it used
its face to dig up tree roots to eat. The skin on
its face was plenty tough.

name: Bastiodon
attack: [{"info": "{MMC} Headbang 80", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Guarded Grill", "effect": "If any damage is done to this Pok\u00e9mon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, this Pok\u00e9mon takes \u2212100 damage from that attack."}]
text:
The bones of its face are huge and hard, so
they were mistaken for its spine until after this
Pokémon was successfully restored.

name: Wormadam
attack: [{"info": "{MM} Iron Head 50+", "effect": "Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads."}]
text:
Its appearance changes depending on where it
evolved. The materials on hand become a part of
its body.

name: Probopass
attack: [{"info": "{MMMC} Triple Nose 30+", "effect": "Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 more damage for each heads."}]
text:
Although it can control its units known as
Mini-Noses, they sometimes get lost and don’t
come back.

name: Gible
attack: [{"info": "{C} Gnaw 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy
passes by, it leaps out and chomps them.
The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

name: Gabite
attack: [{"info": "{WF} Slash 60", "effect": ""}]
text:
In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales.
Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient
will make a weary body feel invigorated.

name: Garchomp
attack: [{"info": "{WF} Dragon Claw 100", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Reckless Shearing", "effect": "You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw a card."}]
text:
It is said that when one runs at high speed,
its wings create blades of wind that can fell
nearby trees.

name: Lickitung
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Tongue Slap 50", "effect": ""}]
text:
If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and
you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in.
The itch won’t go away, either.

name: Lickilicky ex
attack: [{"info": "{CCCC} Licking Fury 100+", "effect": "Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Porygon
attack: [{"info": "{C} Beam 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
State-of-the-art technology was used to create
Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokémon to be
created via computer programming.

name: Porygon2
attack: [{"info": "{C} Sharpen 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
This is a Porygon that was updated with special
data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about
many different subjects all on its own.

name: Porygon-Z
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Buggy Beam 80", "effect": "Change the type of the next Energy that will be generated for your opponent to 1 of the following at random: {G},{R},{W},{L},{P},{F},{D}, or {M}."}]
text:
Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to
move between dimensions, but the program also
caused instability in Porygon-Z’s behavior.

name: Ambipom
attack: [{"info": "{C} Double Hit 40x", "effect": "Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads."}]
text:
It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both
of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze,
that’s proof it really likes you.

name: Starly
attack: [{"info": "{C} Pluck 20", "effect": "Before doing damage, discard all Pok\u00e9mon Tools from your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
They flock around mountains and fields, chasing
after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and
annoying.

name: Staravia
attack: [{"info": "{CC} Wing Attack 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
Recognizing their own weakness, they always live
in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.

name: Staraptor
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Clutch 80", "effect": "During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pok\u00e9mon can't retreat."}]
text:
When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave
the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

name: Glameow
attack: [{"info": "{C} Pose 40", "effect": "Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing."}]
text:
It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate.
Its fickleness is very popular among some.

name: Purugly
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Interrupt 60", "effect": "Your opponent reveals their hand. Choose a card you find there and shuffle it into your opponent's deck."}]
text:
It would claim another Pokémon’s nest as its own
if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.

name: Chatot
attack: [{"info": "{C} Fury Attack 20x", "effect": "Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads."}]
text:
It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them
into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t
attack it.

name: Regigigas
attack: [{"info": "{CCCC} Raging Hammer 50+", "effect": "This attack does more damage equal to the damage this Pok\u00e9mon has on it."}]
text:
It is said to have made Pokémon that look like
itself from a special ice mountain, rocks,
and magma.

rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Weedle
attack: [{"info": "{G} Multiply", "effect": "Put 1 random Weedle from your deck onto your Bench."}]
text:
Often found in forests and grasslands.
It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches
on top of its head.

name: Kakuna
attack: [{"info": "{G} String Shot 20", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Paralyzed."}]
text:
Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only
harden its shell to protect itself when it is
in danger.

name: Beedrill ex
attack: [{"info": "{GG} Crushing Spear 80", "effect": "Discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Pinsir
attack: [{"info": "{GCC} Guillotine Rush 50+", "effect": "Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads."}]
text:
These Pokémon judge one another based on
pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make
for more popularity with the opposite gender.

name: Sprigatito
attack: [{"info": "{G} Cry for Help", "effect": "Put 1 random {G} Pok\u00e9mon from your deck into your hand."}]
text:
Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants.
This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep
it from drying out.

name: Floragato
attack: [{"info": "{GG} Slash 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath
its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against
its opponents.

name: Meowscarada
attack: [{"info": "{GG} Fighting Claws 60+", "effect": "If your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is a Pok\u00e9mon ex, this attack does 70 more damage."}]
text:
This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its
cape to camouflage the stem of its flower,
creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

name: Charmander
attack: [{"info": "{R} Combustion 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It has a preference for hot things. When it rains,
steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

name: Charmeleon
attack: [{"info": "{RR} Combustion 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its
fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

name: Charizard ex
attack: [{"info": "{R} Stoke", "effect": "Take 3 {R} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pok\u00e9mon."}, {"info": "{RRRCC} Steam Artillery 150", "effect": ""}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Magmar
attack: [{"info": "{R} Flare 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it
regrets this habit once it realizes that it has
burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

name: Magmortar
attack: [{"info": "{RRC} Smoke Bomb 70", "effect": "During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pok\u00e9mon tries to use an attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen."}]
text:
When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning
in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to
over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Paldean Tauros
attack: [{"info": "{RCC} Blaze Tackle 80", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon also does 10 damage to itself."}]
text:
When heated by fire energy, its horns can get
hotter than 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. Those
gored by them will suffer both wounds and burns.

name: Tentacool
attack: [{"info": "{W} Rain Splash 10", "effect": ""}]
text:
Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer.
It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it
searches for prey.

name: Tentacruel
attack: [{"info": "{W} Wave Splash 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
When the red orbs on Tentacruel’s head glow
brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to
fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

name: Buizel
attack: [{"info": "{W} Water Gun 10", "effect": ""}]
text:
It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above
water in order to watch for prey movement.

name: Floatzel
attack: [{"info": "{W} Water Arrow", "effect": "This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people
on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

name: Wiglett
attack: [{"info": "{W} Spring Out", "effect": "1 of your opponent's Pok\u00e9mon is chosen at random. Do 30 damage to it."}]
text:
This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza
just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in
the sand.

name: Wugtrio ex
attack: [{"info": "{WWW} Pop Out Throughout", "effect": "1 of your opponent's Pok\u00e9mon is chosen at random 3 times. For each time a Pok\u00e9mon was chosen, do 50 damage to it."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Dondozo
attack: [{"info": "{WWCC} Ocean Cyclone 80", "effect": "This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting
food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

name: Tatsugiri
attack: [{"info": "{W} Rain Splash 20", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Retreat Directive", "effect": "Your Active Dondozo has no Retreat Cost."}]
text:
This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the
mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies
on the outside.

name: Pikachu ex
attack: [{"info": "{LLL} Thunderbolt 150", "effect": "Discard all Energy from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Voltorb
attack: [{"info": "{L} Lightning Ball 10", "effect": ""}]
text:
It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden
jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Electrode
attack: [{"info": "{LL} Tumbling Attack 50+", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage."}]
text:
The more energy it charges up, the faster
it gets. But this also makes it more likely
to explode.

name: Pachirisu
attack: [{"info": "{L} Plasma 10", "effect": "Take a {L} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched {L} Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It’s one of the kinds of Pokémon with electric
cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

name: Pawmi
attack: [{"info": "{L} Punch 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks.
These sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi
rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.

name: Pawmo
attack: [{"info": "{LL} Punch 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
When its group is attacked, Pawmo is the first
to leap into battle, defeating enemies with a
fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.

name: Pawmot
attack: [{"info": "{LL} Electric Punch 70", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Counterattack", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent\u2019s Pok\u00e9mon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once
it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies
with lightning-fast movements.

name: Abra
attack: [{"info": "{P} Psyshot 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it
sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the
powers that the Pokémon wields.

name: Kadabra
attack: [{"info": "{P} Psyshot 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it
sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

name: Alakazam
attack: [{"info": "{PP} Psychic Suppression 80", "effect": "This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon that has any Energy attached."}]
text:
It has an incredibly high level of intelligence.
Some say that Alakazam remembers everything
that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

name: Mr. Mime
attack: [{"info": "{PC} Juggling 20x", "effect": "Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads."}]
text:
The broadness of its hands may be no
coincidence—many scientists believe its palms
became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

name: Drifloon
attack: [{"info": "{P} Ram 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It is whispered that any child who mistakes
Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could
wind up missing.

name: Drifblim
attack: [{"info": "{P} Gust 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
It can generate and release gas within its body.
That’s how it can control the altitude of its drift.

name: Giratina ex
attack: [{"info": "{PPPC} Chaotic Impact 130", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon also does 20 damage to itself."}]
ability: [{"info": "Broken-Space Bellow", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may take a Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pok\u00e9mon. If you use this Ability, your turn ends."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Gimmighoul
attack: [{"info": "{C} Chest-ouflage", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from\u2014and effects of\u2014attacks done to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest
about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force
out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

name: Machop
attack: [{"info": "{F} Low Kick 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
Its whole body is composed of muscles.
Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can
hurl 100 grown-ups.

name: Machoke
attack: [{"info": "{FF} Pummel 30+", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage."}]
text:
Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a
power-save belt to be able to regulate
its motions.

name: Machamp
attack: [{"info": "{FF} Power Press 70+", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon has at least 2 extra {F} Energy attached, this attack does 50 more damage."}]
text:
It quickly swings its four arms to rock its
opponents with ceaseless punches and chops
from all angles.

name: Hitmonlee
attack: [{"info": "{F} Kick 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
This amazing Pokémon has an awesome sense of
balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

name: Hitmonchan
attack: [{"info": "{FFF} Magnum Punch 90", "effect": ""}]
text:
Its punches slice the air. They are launched at
such high speed, even a slight graze could cause
a burn.

name: Riolu
attack: [{"info": "{FF} Punch 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
They communicate with one another using their
auras. They are able to run all through the night.

name: Lucario ex
attack: [{"info": "{FFF} Aura Sphere 100", "effect": "This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Flamigo
attack: [{"info": "{FF} Double Kick 50x", "effect": "Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads."}]
text:
This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck
into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does
not escape from its beak.

name: Ekans
attack: [{"info": "{DC} Ram 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger
than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.

name: Arbok
attack: [{"info": "{DDC} Venomous Fang 70", "effect": "Your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Poisoned."}]
text:
After stunning its opponents with the pattern
on its stomach, it quickly wraps them up in its
body and waits for them to stop moving.

name: Paldean Wooper
attack: [{"info": "{D} Poison Jab 10", "effect": "Your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Poisoned."}]
text:
After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began
living on land. The Pokémon changed over time,
developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

name: Paldean Clodsire ex
attack: [{"info": "{DD} Venoshock 60+", "effect": "If your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is Poisoned, this attack does 60 more damage."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Spiritomb
attack: [{"info": "{D} Confuse Ray 20", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Confused."}]
text:
Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted
in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a
mysterious spell.

name: Shroodle
attack: [{"info": "{D} Gnaw 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
Though usually a mellow Pokémon, it will sink its
sharp, poison-soaked front teeth into any that
anger it, causing paralysis in the object of its ire.

name: Grafaiai
attack: [{"info": "{DD} Bite 40", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Poison Coating", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Poisoned."}]
text:
The color of the poisonous saliva depends on
what the Pokémon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers
in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.

name: Tinkatink
attack: [{"info": "{M} Corkscrew Punch 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It swings its handmade hammer around to protect
itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon
that eat metal.

name: Tinkatuff
attack: [{"info": "{MM} Tenacious Hammer 30+", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage."}]
text:
This Pokémon will attack groups of Pawniard and
Bisharp, gathering metal from them in order to
create a large and sturdy hammer.

name: Tinkaton ex
attack: [{"info": "{MMC} Terrific Thumping 80+", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 more damage."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Varoom
attack: [{"info": "{M} Headbutt 10", "effect": ""}]
text:
It is said that this Pokémon was born when an
unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited
an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

name: Revavroom
attack: [{"info": "{MMC} Spinning Drift 70", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from\u2014and effects of\u2014attacks done to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from
rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders—
now numbering eight—to generate energy.

name: Gholdengo
attack: [{"info": "{MCC} Scintillating Surfing 50x", "effect": "Flip a coin for each {M} Energy attached to this Pok\u00e9mon. This attack does 50 damage for each heads."}]
text:
Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins.
This Pokémon gets along well with others and is
quick to make friends with anybody.

name: Rattata
attack: [{"info": "{C} Tackle 10", "effect": ""}]
text:
Its incisors grow continuously throughout its life.
If its incisors get too long, this Pokémon
becomes unable to eat, and it starves to death.

name: Raticate
attack: [{"info": "{CC} Tackle 50", "effect": ""}]
text:
People say that it fled from its enemies by
using its small webbed hind feet to swim
from island to island in Alola.

name: Jigglypuff
attack: [{"info": "{C} Rollout 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It hugely inflates its stomach and sings a
mysterious melody. If you hear this melody,
you’ll become sleepy right away.

name: Wigglytuff
attack: [{"info": "{CC} Gentle Slap 50", "effect": ""}]
ability: [{"info": "Comforting Song", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from your Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it
angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a
body slam.

name: Lickitung
attack: [{"info": "{CC} Rollout 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and
you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in.
The itch won’t go away, either.

name: Lickilicky
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Rollout 70", "effect": ""}]
text:
Lickilicky’s strange tongue can stretch to many
times the length of its body. No one has figured
out how Lickilicky’s tongue can stretch so far.

name: Bidoof
attack: [{"info": "{CC} Headbutt 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is
more agile and active than it appears.

name: Bibarel ex
attack: [{"info": "{CCCC} Carefree Press 100", "effect": "Heal 30 damage from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Buneary
attack: [{"info": "{C} Pound 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up, something
is wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign the
Pokémon is in need of care.

name: Lopunny
attack: [{"info": "{C} Hopping Shot 30", "effect": ""}]
text:
Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings.
If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds
with superdestructive kicks.

name: Cyclizar
attack: [{"info": "{C} Overacceleration 20", "effect": "During your next turn, this Pok\u00e9mon's Overacceleration attack does +20 damage."}]
text:
Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to
ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of
this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

attack: [{"info": "{PPPC} Chaotic Impact 130", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon also does 20 damage to itself."}]
ability: [{"info": "Broken-Space Bellow", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may take a Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pok\u00e9mon. If you use this Ability, your turn ends."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Weedle
attack: [{"info": "{G} Multiply", "effect": "Put 1 random Weedle from your deck onto your Bench."}]
text:
Often found in forests and grasslands.
It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches
on top of its head.

name: Kakuna
attack: [{"info": "{G} String Shot 20", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon is now Paralyzed."}]
text:
Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only
harden its shell to protect itself when it is
in danger.

name: Charmander
attack: [{"info": "{R} Combustion 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
It has a preference for hot things. When it rains,
steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

name: Charmeleon
attack: [{"info": "{RR} Combustion 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its
fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

name: Wiglett
attack: [{"info": "{W} Spring Out", "effect": "1 of your opponent's Pok\u00e9mon is chosen at random. Do 30 damage to it."}]
text:
This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza
just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in
the sand.

name: Dondozo
attack: [{"info": "{WWCC} Ocean Cyclone 80", "effect": "This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting
food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

name: Pachirisu
attack: [{"info": "{L} Plasma 10", "effect": "Take a {L} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched {L} Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It’s one of the kinds of Pokémon with electric
cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

name: Riolu
attack: [{"info": "{FF} Punch 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
They communicate with one another using their
auras. They are able to run all through the night.

name: Varoom
attack: [{"info": "{M} Headbutt 10", "effect": ""}]
text:
It is said that this Pokémon was born when an
unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited
an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

name: Revavroom
attack: [{"info": "{MMC} Spinning Drift 70", "effect": "Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from\u2014and effects of\u2014attacks done to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from
rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders—
now numbering eight—to generate energy.

name: Beedrill ex
attack: [{"info": "{GG} Crushing Spear 80", "effect": "Discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Charizard ex
attack: [{"info": "{R} Stoke", "effect": "Take 3 {R} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pok\u00e9mon."}, {"info": "{RRRCC} Steam Artillery 150", "effect": ""}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Wugtrio ex
attack: [{"info": "{WWW} Pop Out Throughout", "effect": "1 of your opponent's Pok\u00e9mon is chosen at random 3 times. For each time a Pok\u00e9mon was chosen, do 50 damage to it."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Lucario ex
attack: [{"info": "{FFF} Aura Sphere 100", "effect": "This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Poké Ball
rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Masquerain
text:
It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in
any direction—to and fro and sideways.

name: Karrablast
text:
Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways.
The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.

name: Phantump
text:
After a lost child perished in the forest,
their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing
the spirit’s rebirth as this Pokémon.

name: Trevenant
text:
People fear it due to a belief that it devours any
who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the
Pokémon it shares its woods with, it’s kind.

name: Rowlet
text:
It sends its feathers, which are as sharp
as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong,
so its kicks are also formidable.

name: Fomantis
text:
Fomantis hates having its naps interrupted.
It fires off beams using energy it gathers by
bathing in the sun.

name: Lurantis
text:
By masquerading as a bug Pokémon, it lowers the
guard of actual bug Pokémon lured in by a scent of
sweet flowers. Its sickles bring them down.

name: Bounsweet
text:
Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled-down
fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in
the past, when sweeteners were scarce.

name: Steenee
text:
Steenee spreads a sweet scent that
makes others feel invigorated. This same
scent is popular for antiperspirants.

name: Tsareena
text:
This Pokémon is proud and aggressive. However, it is
said that a Tsareena will instantly become calm if
someone touches the crown on its calyx.

name: Wimpod
ability: [{"info": "Wimp Out", "effect": "During your first turn, this Pok\u00e9mon has no Retreat Cost."}]
text:
It’s nature’s cleaner—it eats anything and everything,
including garbage and rotten things. The ground near
its nest is always clean.

name: Golisopod
text:
It will do anything to win, taking advantage
of every opening and finishing opponents
off with the small claws on its front legs.

name: Dhelmise ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Tapu Bulu
text:
Although it’s called a guardian deity, it’s violent
enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

name: Growlithe
text:
It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly
stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Fletchinder
text:
Fletchinder scatters embers in tall grass
where bug Pokémon might be hiding and
then catches them as they come leaping out.

name: Talonflame
text:
It has top-notch flying capabilities. It flies
around easily, even while carrying prey
that weighs more than 220 lbs.

name: Litten
text:
If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t
open up to you. Even if you do grow close,
giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

name: Torracat
text:
Torracat will let its Trainer coddle it once they’ve
grown close, but it’s a powerful, sharp-clawed
Pokémon, so its Trainer gets covered in scratches.

name: Incineroar ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Salandit
text:
It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow,
rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic
gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

name: Salazzle
text:
Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with
poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring
movements to turn them into loyal servants.

name: Alolan Sandslash
text:
It uses large, hooked claws to cut a path through
deep snow as it runs. On snowy mountains, this
Sandslash is faster than any other Pokémon.

name: Shellder
text:
It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond.
Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

name: Cloyster
text:
Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents
grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.

name: Popplio
text:
The balloons it inflates with its nose grow
larger and larger as it practices day by day.

name: Crabominable ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Dewpider
text:
It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body
and then covers its head with it. Meeting another
Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.

name: Araquanid
text:
It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the
bubbles. This Pokémon can then take its time to savor its meal.

name: Pikachu
text:
When it is angered, it immediately discharges the
energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Alolan Raichu ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Alolan Geodude
text:
If you mistake it for a rock and step on it,
it will headbutt you in anger. In addition to
the pain, it will also zap you with a shock.

name: Alolan Graveler
text:
When two Graveler fight each other, it fills the
surroundings with flashes of light and sound.
People call it the “fireworks of the earth.”

name: Alolan Golem
text:
It’s grumpy and stubborn. If you upset it,
it discharges electricity from the surface of
its body and growls with a voice like thunder.

name: Helioptile
text:
When spread, the frills on its head act like solar
panels, generating the power behind this
Pokémon’s electric moves.

name: Oricorio
ability: [{"info": "Safeguard", "effect": "Prevent all damage done to this Pok\u00e9mon by attacks from your opponent\u2019s Pok\u00e9mon ex."}]
text:
This form of Oricorio has sipped yellow nectar.
It uses nimble steps to approach opponents,
then knocks them out with electric punches.

name: Tapu Koko
text:
Although it’s called a guardian deity, if a
person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood,
it will become a malevolent deity and attack.

name: Mr. Mime
text:
The broadness of its hands may be no
coincidence—many scientists believe its palms
became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

name: Grumpig
text:
It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes.
Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.

name: Oricorio
text:
This form of Oricorio has sipped pink nectar.
It elevates its mind with the gentle steps of its
dance, then unleashes its psychic energy.

name: Cutiefly
text:
Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare.
In fields of flowers, it gets into skirmishes
with Butterfree over food.

name: Ribombee
text:
It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar.
The puffs’ effects depend on the type of
ingredients and how much of each one is used.

name: Comfey
ability: [{"info": "Flower Shield", "effect": "Each of your Pok\u00e9mon that has any Energy attached recovers from all Special Conditions and can\u2019t be affected by any Special Conditions."}]
text:
Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates
itself with them. For some reason, flowers won’t
wither once they’re attached to a Comfey.

name: Sandygast
text:
If it loses its shovel, it will stick something
else—like a branch—in its head to make
do until it finds another shovel.

name: Palossand
text:
The terrifying Palossand drags smaller Pokémon
into its sandy body. Once its victims are trapped,
it drains them of their vitality whenever it pleases.

name: Cosmoem
text:
The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it
the “cocoon of the stars” and built an altar to worship it.

name: Makuhita
text:
It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is
a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.

name: Solrock
text:
When it rotates itself, it gives off light
similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.

name: Crabrawler
text:
This Pokémon punches trees and eats
the berries that drop down, training itself
and getting food at the same time.

name: Rockruff
text:
This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young.
Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures,
but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

name: Lycanroc
text:
Lycanroc attacks its prey with its
sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys
the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.

name: Mudbray
text:
This Pokémon covers itself in mud that it
has regurgitated. The mud won’t dry out even
if it’s exposed to the sun for a long time.

name: Mudsdale
text:
This Pokémon has been treasured not just
for its physical labor but also because it produces
high-quality mud used for making pottery.

name: Alolan Meowth
text:
It’s accustomed to luxury because it
used to live with Alolan royalty. As a
result, it’s very picky about food.

name: Alolan Persian
ability: [{"info": "Fur Coat", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon takes \u221220 damage from attacks."}]
text:
The round face of Alolan Persian is considered
to be a symbol of prosperity in the Alola region,
so these Pokémon are very well cared for.

name: Trubbish
text:
Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you
leave trash lying around, you could even find
one of these Pokémon living in your room.

name: Alolan Diglett
text:
The metal-rich geology of this Pokémon’s habitat
caused it to develop steel whiskers on its head.

name: Alolan Dugtrio
text:
Their beautiful, metallic whiskers create a sort of
protective helmet on their heads, and they also
function as highly precise sensors.

name: Excadrill
text:
It’s not uncommon for tunnels that appear to
have formed naturally to actually be a result
of Excadrill’s rampant digging.

name: Escavalier
text:
Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet,
they defend themselves and attack with two lances.

name: Klefki
text:
Once it absorbs a key’s metal ions, it discards the
key without a second thought. However, it will
hang on to keys it favors for decades.

name: Solgaleo ex
ability: [{"info": "Rising Road", "effect": "Once during your turn, if this Pok\u00e9mon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Magearna
text:
It synchronizes its consciousness with others
to understand their feelings. This faculty makes
it useful for taking care of people.

name: Drampa
text:
The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles
in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play
with the children living in the towns below.

name: Fletchling
text:
This Pokémon is normally calm, but once it enters battle,
its hormonal balance changes and it becomes aggressive.

name: Hawlucha
text:
Its elegant finishing moves—performed by nimbly
leaping around using its wings—are polished in
the forest where it was born and raised.

name: Trumbeak
text:
It can bend the tip of its beak to produce
over a hundred different cries at will.

name: Toucannon
text:
They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate.
The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.

name: Yungoos
text:
Its stomach fills most of its torso. It wanders the
same path every day, searching for fresh food.

name: Gumshoos
text:
Once it finds signs of prey, it will patiently stake
out the location, waiting until the sun goes down.

name: Komala
ability: [{"info": "Comatose", "effect": "As long as this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot, whenever you attach an Energy from your Energy Zone to it, it is now Asleep."}]
text:
Komala spends its entire life sleeping.
It feeds on leaves that contain a potent
poison only Komala can break down.

rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Lillie
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Bulbasaur
text:
There is a plant seed on its back right from the
day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly
grows larger.

name: Ivysaur
text:
When the bulb on its back grows large, it
appears to lose the ability to stand on its
hind legs.

name: Venusaur
text:
Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar
energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

name: Staryu
text:
If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you’ll
be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a
steady rhythm.

name: Starmie
text:
This Pokémon has an organ known as its core.
The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is
unleashing its potent psychic powers.

name: Machop
text:
Its whole body is composed of muscles.
Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can
hurl 100 grown-ups.

name: Machoke
text:
Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a
power-save belt to be able to regulate
its motions.

name: Machamp
text:
It quickly swings its four arms to rock its
opponents with ceaseless punches and chops
from all angles.

name: Jigglypuff
text:
When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously
soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

name: Wigglytuff
ability: [{"info": "Comforting Song", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from your Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it
angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a
body slam.

name: Venusaur ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.
