rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Lunala ex
ability: [{"info": "Psychic Connect", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may move all Energy from 1 of your Benched Pok\u00e9mon to your Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Solgaleo ex
ability: [{"info": "Rising Road", "effect": "Once during your turn, if this Pok\u00e9mon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Exeggcute
text:
Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs,
it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates
with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

name: Alolan Exeggutor
text:
Blazing sunlight has brought out the true
form and powers of this Pokémon.

name: Surskit
text:
They usually live on ponds, but after an evening
shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.

name: Maractus
text:
With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles
of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling
bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.

name: Rowlet
text:
It sends its feathers, which are as sharp
as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong,
so its kicks are also formidable.

name: Dartrix
text:
This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you
don’t groom it diligently, it may stop listening to you.

name: Decidueye ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Grubbin
text:
Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting
caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.

name: Morelull
text:
Pokémon living in the forest eat the
delicious caps on Morelull’s head.
The caps regrow overnight.

name: Shiinotic
text:
Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to
sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing,
it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

name: Arcanine
text:
An ancient picture scroll shows that people
were captivated by its movement as it ran
through prairies.

name: Alolan Marowak
text:
This Pokémon sets the bone it holds
on fire and dances through the night
as a way to mourn its fallen allies.

name: Litten
text:
If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t
open up to you. Even if you do grow close,
giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

name: Oricorio
text:
This form of Oricorio has sipped red nectar. It whips up
blazing flames as it moves to the steps of its passionate dance.

name: Turtonator
text:
Explosive substances coat the shell on
its back. Enemies that dare attack it will
be blown away by an immense detonation.

name: Alolan Sandshrew
text:
Life on mountains covered with deep snow has granted
this Pokémon a body of ice that’s as hard as steel.

name: Alolan Vulpix
text:
After long years in the ever-snowcapped mountains
of Alola, this Vulpix has gained power over ice.

name: Alolan Ninetales
text:
A deity resides in the snowy mountains
where this Pokémon lives. In ancient times,
it was worshiped as that deity’s incarnation.

name: Lapras
text:
A smart and kindhearted Pokémon,
it glides across the surface of the sea while
its beautiful song echoes around it.

name: Popplio
text:
The balloons it inflates with its nose grow
larger and larger as it practices day by day.

name: Brionne
text:
It gets excited when it sees a dance it
doesn’t know. This hard worker practices
diligently until it can learn that dance.

name: Primarina
ability: [{"info": "Melodious Healing", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may heal 30 damage from each of your Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes
down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.

name: Wishiwashi
text:
Individually, they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering
up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.

name: Wishiwashi ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Pyukumuku
ability: [{"info": "Innards Out", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent\u2019s Pok\u00e9mon, do 50 damage to the Attacking Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a
foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means
to punch them.

name: Bruxish
text:
It grinds its teeth with great force to stimulate
its brain. It fires the psychic energy created by
this process from the protuberance on its head.

name: Tapu Fini
text:
This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates
water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog,
it came to be both feared and revered.

name: Heliolisk
text:
One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill
outspread is all it would take to produce enough
electricity to power a city.

name: Charjabug
text:
While its durable shell protects it from attacks,
Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of
electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

name: Vikavolt
text:
It builds up electricity in its abdomen,
focuses it through its jaws, and then fires
the electricity off in concentrated beams.

name: Togedemaru
text:
With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon
takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon.
It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

name: Sableye
text:
It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its
sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

name: Spoink
text:
Spoink will die if it stops bouncing. The pearl
on its head amplifies its psychic powers.

name: Lunatone
text:
The phase of the moon apparently has some effect
on its power. It’s active on the night of a full moon.

name: Shuppet
text:
It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice.
Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.

name: Banette
text:
This Pokémon developed from an abandoned doll
that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.

name: Oricorio
text:
This form of Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. It uses
ethereal dance steps to call forth the spirits of the dead.

name: Mimikyu
text:
There was a scientist who peeked under
Mimikyu’s old rag in the name of research.
The scientist died of a mysterious disease.

name: Tapu Lele
text:
It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon
by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales.
This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

name: Cosmog
text:
Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown
away by the slightest breeze, it doesn’t seem to care.

name: Lunala ex
ability: [{"info": "Psychic Connect", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may move all Energy from 1 of your Benched Pok\u00e9mon to your Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Necrozma
text:
It looks somehow pained as it rages around
in search of light, which serves as its energy.
It’s apparently from another world.

name: Cubone
text:
When the memory of its departed mother brings
it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the
skull it wears on its head.

name: Hariyama
text:
It loves challenging others to tests of strength.
It has the power to stop a train with a slap.

name: Drilbur
text:
It brings its claws together and whirls around
at high speed before rushing toward its prey.

name: Timburr
text:
It loves helping out with construction projects.
It loves it so much that if rain causes work to
halt, it swings its log around and throws a tantrum.

name: Gurdurr
text:
It shows off its muscles to Machoke and
other Gurdurr. If it fails to measure up to the
other Pokémon, it lies low for a little while.

name: Conkeldurr
ability: [{"info": "Guts", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this Pok\u00e9mon is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10."}]
text:
Concrete mixed by Conkeldurr is much more
durable than normal concrete, even when the
compositions of the two materials are the same.

name: Rockruff
text:
This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young.
Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures,
but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

name: Lycanroc
text:
This Pokémon uses its rocky mane to slash
any who approach. It will even disobey its
Trainer if it dislikes the orders it was given.

name: Passimian ex
ability: [{"info": "Offload Pass", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent\u2019s Pok\u00e9mon, move all Energy from this Pok\u00e9mon to 1 of your Benched Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Minior
text:
Places where Minior fall from the night
sky are few and far between, with Alola
being one of the precious few.

name: Alolan Rattata
text:
It shows no interest in anything that
isn’t fresh. If you take it shopping with
you, it will help you pick out ingredients.

name: Alolan Raticate
text:
It has an incredibly greedy personality. Its nest
is filled with so much food gathered by Rattata
at its direction, it can’t possibly eat it all.

name: Alolan Grimer
text:
There are a hundred or so of them living in
Alola’s waste-disposal site. They’re all hard
workers who eat a lot of trash.

name: Alolan Muk ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Absol
text:
Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and
mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely
sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

name: Garbodor
text:
This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison
inside its body. The main component of the
poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

name: Mareanie
text:
This Pokémon wanders the seaside looking for
food. It often gets electric shocks from broken
Pincurchin spines that it tries to eat.

name: Toxapex
text:
This Pokémon lives within a dome made by its
own legs. Toxapex monitors its surroundings by
sensing the flow of the tide through its spikes.

name: Jangmo-o
text:
They learn to fight by smashing their head scales together.
The dueling strengthens both their skills and their spirits.

name: Hakamo-o
text:
The scaleless, scarred parts of its
body are signs of its strength. It shows
them off to defeated opponents.

name: Kommo-o
text:
It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents.
This Pokémon will battle only those who stand
steadfast in the face of this display.

name: Tauros
text:
When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails,
it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to
charge with astounding speed.

name: Skitty
text:
It can’t stop itself from chasing moving things,
and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.

name: Delcatty
text:
It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a
comfortable place in which to groom itself.

name: Pikipek
text:
It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some
idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.

name: Stufful
text:
Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out
to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.

name: Bewear
text:
Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show
its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is
dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

name: Oranguru
text:
People used to mistake Oranguru for a human
when they saw it issue command after command
to the other Pokémon of the forest.

name: Fishing Net
rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Acerola
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Ilima
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Kiawe
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Guzma
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Alolan Exeggutor
text:
Blazing sunlight has brought out the true
form and powers of this Pokémon.

name: Morelull
text:
Pokémon living in the forest eat the
delicious caps on Morelull’s head.
The caps regrow overnight.

name: Alolan Marowak
text:
This Pokémon sets the bone it holds
on fire and dances through the night
as a way to mourn its fallen allies.

name: Turtonator
text:
Explosive substances coat the shell on
its back. Enemies that dare attack it will
be blown away by an immense detonation.

name: Alolan Vulpix
text:
After long years in the ever-snowcapped mountains
of Alola, this Vulpix has gained power over ice.

name: Pyukumuku
ability: [{"info": "Innards Out", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent\u2019s Pok\u00e9mon, do 50 damage to the Attacking Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a
foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means
to punch them.

name: Tapu Fini
text:
This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates
water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog,
it came to be both feared and revered.

name: Tapu Lele
text:
It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon
by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales.
This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

name: Cosmog
text:
Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown
away by the slightest breeze, it doesn’t seem to care.

name: Minior
text:
Places where Minior fall from the night
sky are few and far between, with Alola
being one of the precious few.

name: Pikipek
text:
It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some
idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.

name: Bewear
text:
Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show
its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is
dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Alolan Muk ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Guzma
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Exeggcute
text:
Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs,
it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates
with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

name: Exeggutor
text:
Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking
different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be
very interested in one another.

name: Squirtle
text:
When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it
squirts out water with vigorous force.

name: Wartortle
text:
It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its
shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

name: Blastoise
text:
It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause
fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

name: Gastly
text:
It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body,
slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it
through the skin.

name: Haunter
text:
It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders
with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless
shuddering.

name: Gengar
text:
To steal the life of its target, it slips into
the prey’s shadow and silently waits for
an opportunity.

name: Cubone
text:
When the memory of its departed mother brings
it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the
skull it wears on its head.

name: Marowak
text:
This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a
sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents
bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

name: Exeggutor ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Blastoise ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Gengar ex
ability: [{"info": "Shadowy Spellbind", "effect": "As long as this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can\u2019t use any Supporter cards from their hand."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Marowak ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Petilil
text:
The leaves on its head grow right back even if
they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those
who eat them.

name: Lilligant
text:
The fragrance of the garland on its head has
a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very
difficult.

name: Rowlet
text:
It sends its feathers, which are as sharp
as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong,
so its kicks are also formidable.

name: Dartrix
text:
This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you
don’t groom it diligently, it may stop listening to you.

name: Decidueye
text:
It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at
opponents. When it simply can’t afford to miss,
it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.

name: Buzzwole ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Pheromosa
text:
A life-form that lives in another world, its body
is thin and supple, but it also possesses
great power.

name: Kartana
text:
This Ultra Beast’s body, which is as thin
as paper, is like a sharpened sword.

name: Blacephalon
text:
It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the
explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

name: Mantine
text:
If it builds up enough speed swimming, it
can jump out above the waves and glide
for over 300 feet.

name: Carvanha
text:
It won’t attack while it’s alone—not even if it
spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to
join it, and then the Pokémon attack as a group.

name: Sharpedo
text:
As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo
will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling
toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

name: Shinx
text:
The extension and contraction of its muscles
generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

name: Luxio
text:
Strong electricity courses through the tips of
its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting
in foes.

name: Luxray
ability: [{"info": "Intimidating Fang", "effect": "As long as this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot, attacks used by your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon do \u221220 damage."}]
text:
It can see clearly through walls to track down its
prey and seek its lost young.

name: Blitzle
text:
When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear.
It can catch lightning with its mane and store
the electricity.

name: Zebstrika
text:
When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it
shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

name: Emolga
text:
As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles
with electricity. This Pokémon is cute, but it can
cause a lot of trouble.

name: Tapu Koko ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Xurkitree
text:
Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently
a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Zeraora
ability: [{"info": "Thunderclap Flash", "effect": "At the end of your first turn, take a Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents
apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack,
they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

name: Clefairy
text:
It is said that happiness will come to those who
see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a
full moon.

name: Clefable
text:
A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will
run and hide the moment it senses people.

name: Phantump
text:
With a voice like a human child’s, it cries out to
lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost
among the trees.

name: Trevenant
text:
People fear it due to a belief that it devours any
who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the
Pokémon it shares its woods with, it’s kind.

name: Morelull
text:
It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone
seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

name: Shiinotic
ability: [{"info": "Illuminate", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may put a random Pok\u00e9mon from your deck into your hand."}]
text:
Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to
sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing,
it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

name: Meditite
text:
It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens
its inner strength through meditation.

name: Medicham
text:
Through yoga training, it gained the psychic
power to predict its foe’s next move.

name: Baltoy
text:
It moves while spinning around on its single foot.
Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on
their heads.

name: Claydol
ability: [{"info": "Heal Block", "effect": "Pok\u00e9mon (both yours and your opponent\u2019s) can\u2019t be healed."}]
text:
This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient
clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.

name: Rockruff
text:
This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young.
Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures,
but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

name: Lycanroc ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Passimian
text:
This Pokémon battles by throwing hard berries.
It won’t obey a Trainer who throws Poké Balls
without skill.

name: Sandygast
text:
If it loses its shovel, it will stick something
else—like a branch—in its head to make
do until it finds another shovel.

name: Palossand
text:
The terrifying Palossand drags smaller Pokémon
into its sandy body. Once its victims are trapped,
it drains them of their vitality whenever it pleases.

name: Alolan Meowth
text:
It’s accustomed to luxury because it
used to live with Alolan royalty. As a
result, it’s very picky about food.

name: Alolan Persian
text:
The round face of Alolan Persian is considered
to be a symbol of prosperity in the Alola region,
so these Pokémon are very well cared for.

name: Sandile
text:
It submerges itself in sand and moves as if
swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies
from finding it and maintains its temperature.

name: Krokorok
text:
Protected by thin membranes, their eyes can see
even in the dead of night. They live in groups of
a few individuals.

name: Krookodile
text:
After clamping down with its powerful jaws, it
twists its body around to rip its prey in half.

name: Nihilego
ability: [{"info": "More Poison", "effect": "Your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon takes +10 damage from being Poisoned."}]
text:
A life-form from another world, it was dubbed
a UB and is thought to produce a
strong neurotoxin.

name: Guzzlord ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Poipole
text:
This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be
chosen as a first partner in its own world.

name: Naganadel
text:
It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid
inside its body. It is one of the organisms known
as UBs.

name: Alolan Diglett
text:
The metal-rich geology of this Pokémon’s habitat
caused it to develop steel whiskers on its head.

name: Alolan Dugtrio ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Aron
text:
It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks—
to build up the steel armor that protects its body.

name: Lairon
text:
It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory
by bashing one another with their steel bodies.

name: Aggron
text:
Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate
thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by
ramming into them horn first.

name: Ferroseed
text:
It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging
to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

name: Ferrothorn
ability: [{"info": "Steel Spikes", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent\u2019s Pok\u00e9mon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks,
and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb
the nutrients it finds within the stone.

name: Stakataka
text:
It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one
appears to be made up of many life-forms
stacked one on top of each other.

name: Lillipup
text:
This Pokémon is courageous but also cautious.
It uses the soft fur covering its face to collect
information about its surroundings.

name: Herdier
text:
Herdier is a very smart and friendly Pokémon.
So much so that there’s a theory that Herdier was
the first Pokémon to partner with people.

name: Stoutland
ability: [{"info": "Guard Dog Visage", "effect": "As long as this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot, attacks used by your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon cost 1 more."}]
text:
These Pokémon seem to enjoy living with humans.
Even a Stoutland caught in the wild will warm up
to people in about three days.

name: Stufful
text:
Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out
to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.

name: Bewear
text:
Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show
its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is
dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

name: Oranguru
text:
It normally spends its time meditating in the
treetops. It throws Poké Balls and gives other
Pokémon orders as it pleases.

name: Type: Null
text:
A Pokémon weapon developed for a specific
mission, it went berserk during an experiment,
so it was cryogenically frozen.

name: Silvally
text:
This is its form once it has awakened and
evolved. Freed from its heavy mask, its speed is
greatly increased.

name: Celesteela
ability: [{"info": "Ultra Thrusters", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may switch your Active Ultra Beast with 1 of your Benched Ultra Beasts."}]
text:
One of the dangerous UBs, high energy readings
can be detected coming from both of its
huge arms.

name: Growlithe
text:
It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly
stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Arcanine
text:
An ancient picture scroll shows that people
were captivated by its movement as it ran
through prairies.

name: Froakie
text:
It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back.
The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise
take when attacked.

name: Frogadier
text:
It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise
control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: Greninja
ability: [{"info": "Water Shuriken", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may do 20 damage to 1 of your opponent\u2019s Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It creates throwing stars out of compressed water.
When it spins them and throws them at high speed,
these stars can split metal in two.

name: Jynx
text:
Its strange cries sound like human language.
There are some musicians who compose songs
for Jynx to sing.

name: Pidgey
text:
A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps
its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

name: Pidgeotto
text:
The claws on its feet are well developed.
It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute
to its nest over 60 miles away.

name: Pidgeot
ability: [{"info": "Drive Off", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may switch out your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon to the Bench.\u00a0(Your opponent chooses the new Active Pok\u00e9mon.)"}]
text:
When hunting, it skims the surface of water
at high speed to pick off unwary prey such
as Magikarp.

name: Aerodactyl
text:
This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times.
Apparently even modern technology is incapable
of producing a perfectly restored specimen.

name: Celebi ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Arcanine ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Aerodactyl ex
ability: [{"info": "Primeval Law", "effect": "Your opponent can\u2019t play any Pok\u00e9mon from their hand to evolve their Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Pidgeot ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Nihilego
ability: [{"info": "More Poison", "effect": "Your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon takes +10 damage from being Poisoned."}]
text:
A life-form from another world, it was dubbed
a UB and is thought to produce a
strong neurotoxin.

name: Tropius
text:
It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit
around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows
twice a year.

name: Leafeon
text:
When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of
sunshine, you’ll know it is using photosynthesis
to produce clean air.

name: Bounsweet
text:
Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled-down
fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in
the past, when sweeteners were scarce.

name: Steenee
text:
Steenee spreads a sweet scent that
makes others feel invigorated. This same
scent is popular for antiperspirants.

name: Tsareena
text:
This Pokémon is proud and aggressive. However, it is
said that a Tsareena will instantly become calm if
someone touches the crown on its calyx.

name: Applin
text:
It grows by eating the flesh of an apple.
Applin uses its own body fluid to strengthen
the apple’s skin and prevent it from rotting.

name: Appletun
text:
It feeds mainly on sweet apples. It will also eat
small bug Pokémon that are attracted by its
sweet nectar.

name: Flareon
text:
Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated,
and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000
degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Flareon ex
ability: [{"info": "Combust", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may attach a Energy from your discard pile to this Pok\u00e9mon. If you do, do 20 damage to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Torkoal
text:
It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows
out black soot if it is endangered.

name: Litten
text:
If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t
open up to you. Even if you do grow close,
giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

name: Torracat
text:
Torracat will let its Trainer coddle it once they’ve
grown close, but it’s a powerful, sharp-clawed
Pokémon, so its Trainer gets covered in scratches.

name: Incineroar
text:
Although it’s rough mannered and egotistical, it
finds beating down unworthy opponents boring.
It gets motivated for stronger opponents.

name: Salandit
text:
It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow,
rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic
gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

name: Salazzle
text:
Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with
poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring
movements to turn them into loyal servants.

name: Vaporeon
text:
It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with
a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

name: Glaceon
text:
It can control its body temperature at will.
This enables it to freeze the moisture in the
atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.

name: Vanillite
text:
Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself
comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to
cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.

name: Vanillish
text:
By drinking pure water, it grows its icy body.
This Pokémon can be hard to find on days with
warm, sunny weather.

name: Vanilluxe
text:
When its anger reaches a breaking point, this
Pokémon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes
every creature around it, be they friend or foe.

name: Alomomola
text:
It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its
fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

name: Popplio
text:
The balloons it inflates with its nose grow
larger and larger as it practices day by day.

name: Brionne
text:
It gets excited when it sees a dance it
doesn’t know. This hard worker practices
diligently until it can learn that dance.

name: Primarina ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Jolteon
text:
It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted
by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

name: Joltik
text:
Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon.
It’s soaking up static electricity because it can’t
produce a charge on its own.

name: Galvantula
text:
It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its
means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could
be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.

name: Espeon
text:
The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is
predicting its opponent’s next move.

name: Woobat
text:
While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots
of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it’s
evidence that Woobat live there.

name: Swoobat
text:
Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out.
Afterward, it won’t be able to fly for a
little while.

name: Swirlix
text:
It eats its own weight in sugar every day.
If it doesn’t get enough sugar, it becomes
incredibly grumpy.

name: Slurpuff
text:
By taking in a person’s scent, it can sniff out their
mental and physical condition. It’s hoped that
this skill will have many medical applications.

name: Sylveon
text:
This Pokémon uses its ribbonlike feelers to send
a soothing aura into its opponents, erasing
their hostility.

name: Sylveon ex
ability: [{"info": "Happy Ribbon", "effect": "Once during your turn, when you play this Pok\u00e9mon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pok\u00e9mon, you may draw 2 cards."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Mimikyu
text:
This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by
sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides
itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

name: Milcery
text:
This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling
particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

name: Alcremie
text:
When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them
to berries it’s decorated with cream.

name: Barboach
text:
Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in
muddy waters, it can detect its prey’s location.

name: Whiscash
text:
It is extremely protective of its territory. If any
foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.

name: Mienfoo
text:
In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop
with its arms more than 100 times.

name: Mienshao
text:
When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging
opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the
fur on its arms.

name: Carbink
text:
When beset by attackers, Carbink wipes them all
out by firing high-energy beams from the gems
embedded in its body.

name: Umbreon
text:
When exposed to the moon’s aura, the rings on its
body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.

name: Sableye
text:
Materials from gems it has eaten float to the
surface of its body and can form an infinite
number of patterns among individuals.

name: Purrloin
text:
Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable
behavior come away with stinging scratches from
its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

name: Liepard
text:
Don’t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant
figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

name: Mawile
text:
It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into
complacency, then bites with its huge,
relentless jaws.

name: Togedemaru
text:
With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon
takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon.
It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

name: Meltan
text:
It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid
metal within its body is how it generates energy.

name: Melmetal
text:
At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and
fall apart. The small shards left behind will
eventually be reborn as Meltan.

name: Dratini
text:
It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger.
During this process, it is protected by a rapid
waterfall.

name: Dragonair
text:
They say that if it emits an aura from its whole
body, the weather will begin to change instantly.

name: Dragonite ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Drampa
text:
The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles
in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play
with the children living in the towns below.

name: Eevee
text:
Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to
adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Eevee ex
ability: [{"info": "Veevee \u2019volve", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon can evolve into any Pok\u00e9mon that evolves from Eevee if you play it from your hand onto this Pok\u00e9mon. (This Pok\u00e9mon can\u2019t evolve during your first turn or the turn you play it.)"}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Snorlax ex
ability: [{"info": "Full-Mouth Manner", "effect": "At the end of your turn, if this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot, heal 20 damage from it."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Aipom
text:
As it did more and more with its tail, its hands
became clumsy. It makes its nest high in
the treetops.

name: Ambipom
ability: [{"info": "Catching Tail", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may put a random Pok\u00e9mon Tool card from your deck into your hand."}]
text:
It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both
of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze,
that’s proof it really likes you.

name: Chatot
text:
It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them
into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t
attack it.

name: Audino
text:
This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers,
Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.

name: Minccino
text:
The way it brushes away grime with its tail
can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on
spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.

name: Cinccino
text:
Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads
over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust.
Cinccino won’t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

name: Skwovet
text:
It stores berries in its cheeks. When there are no
berries to be found, Skwovet will stuff pebbles
into its cheeks to stave off its cravings.

name: Greedent
text:
This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping
them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.

name: Eevee Bag
rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Hau
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Penny
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of

and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000
degrees Fahrenheit.

It can control its body temperature at will.

atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.

It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted
by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is
predicting its opponent’s next move.

When exposed to the moon’s aura, the rings on its

Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to
adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Pinsir
text:
These Pokémon judge one another based on
pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make
for more popularity with the opposite gender.

name: Lapras
text:
A smart and kindhearted Pokémon,
it glides across the surface of the sea while
its beautiful song echoes around it.

name: Voltorb
text:
It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden
jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Electrode
text:
The more energy it charges up, the faster
it gets. But this also makes it more likely
to explode.

name: Ralts
text:
The horns on its head provide a strong power
that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

name: Kirlia
text:
It has a psychic power that enables it to distort
the space around it and see into the future.

name: Gardevoir
ability: [{"info": "Psy Shadow", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may take a Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to the Pok\u00e9mon in the Active Spot."}]
text:
To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic
power to create a small black hole.

name: Ekans
text:
By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger
than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.

name: Arbok
text:
The latest research has determined that there
are over 20 possible arrangements of the
patterns on its stomach.

name: Farfetch’d
text:
The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves
as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire
situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

name: Moltres ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Articuno ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Zapdos ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Gallade ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Eevee Bag
rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Tangela
text:
Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows
nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this
Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

name: Tangrowth
text:
Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it
pleases. Recent research has shown that these
arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

name: Hoppip
text:
Outside of cold regions, Hoppip can be found
practically everywhere. This is because the wind
carries this species all over the world.

name: Skiploom
text:
Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a
Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the
flower on the Pokémon’s head.

name: Jumpluff
ability: [{"info": "Fluffy Flight", "effect": "Your Active Pok\u00e9mon has no Retreat Cost."}]
text:
Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its
cotton spores run out, its journey ends, as does
its life.

name: Yanma
text:
Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its
head. It won’t miss prey—even those behind it.

name: Yanmega
text:
It prefers to battle by biting apart foes’ heads
instantly while flying by at high speed.

name: Heracross
text:
It loves sweet nectar. To keep all the nectar to
itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.

name: Cherubi
ability: [{"info": "En-fruits-iastic", "effect": "If this Pok\u00e9mon has a Pok\u00e9mon Tool attached, attacks used by this Pok\u00e9mon cost 1 less Energy."}]
text:
It nimbly dashes about to avoid getting pecked
by bird Pokémon that would love to make off
with its small, nutrient-rich storage ball.

name: Cherrim
text:
After absorbing plenty of sunlight, Cherrim takes
this form. It’s full of energy while it’s like this,
and its liveliness will go on until sundown.

name: Slugma
text:
A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers
around in a constant search for warm places.

name: Magcargo
text:
Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames
that circulate throughout its body.

name: Magby
text:
This Pokémon is still small and timid.
Whenever Magby gets excited or surprised,
flames leak from its mouth and its nose.

name: Entei
text:
A Pokémon that races across the land. It is said
that one is born every time a new volcano appears.

name: Ho-Oh ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Darmanitan
text:
The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon
can deliver punches capable of obliterating a
dump truck.

name: Totodile
text:
It is small but rough and tough. It won’t hesitate to
take a bite out of anything that moves.

name: Croconaw
text:
If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its
place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.

name: Feraligatr
text:
It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding
speed when it attacks and bites prey.

name: Marill
text:
The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can
stay dry even when it plays in the water.

name: Azumarill
ability: [{"info": "Thick Fat", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon takes \u221230 damage from attacks from or Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish
the movements of things in water and tell what
they are.

name: Delibird
text:
It carries food all day long. There are tales about
lost people who were saved by the food it had.

name: Ducklett
text:
When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water,
escaping under cover of the spray.

name: Swanna
text:
Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap
their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.

name: Raikou
text:
The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts
at will. They say that it descended with lightning.

name: Smoochum
text:
If its face gets even slightly dirty, Smoochum will
bathe immediately. But if its body gets dirty,
Smoochum doesn’t really seem to care.

name: Togepi
text:
The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said
that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

name: Togetic
text:
They say that it will appear before kindhearted,
caring people and shower them with happiness.

name: Togekiss
ability: [{"info": "Celestial Blessing", "effect": "If any damage is done to this Pok\u00e9mon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage."}]
text:
These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near
conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they’ve hardly
been seen at all.

name: Unown
ability: [{"info": "GUARD", "effect": "This Ability works if you have any Unown in play with an Ability other than GUARD. All of your Pok\u00e9mon take \u221210 damage from attacks from your opponent\u2019s Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape
appears to have some meaning.

name: Girafarig
text:
Girafarig’s tail has a small head. It instinctively
bites at any foe that approaches the Pokémon
from behind.

name: Munna
text:
Late at night, it appears beside people’s pillows.
As it feeds on dreams, the patterns on its body
give off a faint glow.

name: Musharna
text:
When dark mists emanate from its body, don’t
get too near. If you do, your nightmares will
become reality.

name: Onix
text:
As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many
hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

name: Gligar
text:
It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey,
it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.

name: Gliscor
text:
It observes prey while hanging inverted from
branches. When the chance presents itself,
it swoops!

name: Swinub
text:
It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up
food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

name: Piloswine
text:
If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back
stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

name: Mamoswine
text:
This Pokémon can be spotted in wall paintings
from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a
while, it was thought to have gone extinct.

name: Phanpy
text:
This Pokémon lives and nests on a riverbank.
After playing in the mud, it won’t be able to
settle down unless it washes its body.

name: Donphan ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Tyrogue
text:
It is always bursting with energy. To make itself
stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.

name: Hitmontop
text:
It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high
speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

name: Larvitar
text:
Born deep underground, this Pokémon
becomes a pupa after eating enough
dirt to make a mountain.

name: Pupitar
text:
This pupa flies around wildly by venting with
great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

name: Zubat
text:
It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check
its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies
around with skill.

name: Golbat
text:
It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said
that if it finds others of its kind going hungry,
it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.

name: Crobat ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Spinarak
text:
It lies still in the same pose for days in its web,
waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.

name: Ariados
text:
Every night, it wanders around in search of
prey, whose movements it restrains by spewing
threads before it bites into them with its fangs.

name: Umbreon ex
ability: [{"info": "Dark Chase", "effect": "Once during your turn, if this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot, you may switch in 1 of your opponent\u2019s Benched Pok\u00e9mon that has damage on it to the Active Spot."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Houndour
text:
It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a
variety of cries for communicating with others.

name: Tyranitar
ability: [{"info": "Energy Plunder", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may move all Energy from each of your Pok\u00e9mon to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Extremely strong, it can change the landscape.
It is so insolent that it doesn’t care about others.

name: Absol
text:
Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and
mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely
sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

name: Forretress
text:
It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters
pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.

name: Steelix
text:
It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years,
its composition changes to become diamond-like.

name: Skarmory ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Klink
text:
The two minigears that compose this Pokémon
are closer than twins. They mesh well only with
each other.

name: Klang
text:
When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up
perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and
this Pokémon’s rotation speed increases sharply.

name: Klinklang
text:
From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of
electricity. Its red core contains an enormous
amount of energy.

name: Spearow
text:
Its reckless nature leads it to stand up to
others—even large Pokémon—if it has to protect
its territory.

name: Fearow
text:
Carrying food through Fearow’s territory is
dangerous. It will snatch the food away from
you in a flash!

name: Chansey
text:
This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs
and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

name: Blissey
text:
Anyone who takes even one taste of Blissey’s
egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant
to everyone.

name: Kangaskhan
text:
Although it’s carrying its baby in a pouch on
its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It
intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

name: Sentret
text:
When acting as a lookout, it warns others of danger
by screeching and hitting the ground with its tail.

name: Furret
text:
The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up
around them. It corners foes with speed.

name: Hoothoot
ability: [{"info": "Insomnia", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon can\u2019t be Asleep."}]
text:
It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so
fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

name: Noctowl
text:
Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to
see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

name: Aipom
text:
As it did more and more with its tail, its hands
became clumsy. It makes its nest high in
the treetops.

name: Teddiursa
text:
Its paws are soaked in oodles of honey. When
nervous, Teddiursa will lick its paws and soon
have a smile back on its face.

name: Ursaring
text:
It usually wears a hardened expression, but when
it’s licking up honey—which it loves—the joy it
feels will cause it to break into a wide grin.

name: Stantler
text:
This Pokémon apparently used to live in much
harsher environments, and thus it once had
stronger psychic powers than it does now.

name: Bouffalant
text:
These Pokémon can crush a car with no more
than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on
their heads hold higher positions within the herd.

name: Silver
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Jasmine
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Hiker
rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Heracross
text:
It loves sweet nectar. To keep all the nectar to
itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.

name: Magby
text:
This Pokémon is still small and timid.
Whenever Magby gets excited or surprised,
flames leak from its mouth and its nose.

name: Totodile
text:
It is small but rough and tough. It won’t hesitate to
take a bite out of anything that moves.

name: Delibird
text:
It carries food all day long. There are tales about
lost people who were saved by the food it had.

name: Togepi
text:
The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said
that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

name: Gligar
text:
It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey,
it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.

name: Spinarak
text:
It lies still in the same pose for days in its web,
waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.

name: Tyranitar
ability: [{"info": "Energy Plunder", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may move all Energy from each of your Pok\u00e9mon to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Extremely strong, it can change the landscape.
It is so insolent that it doesn’t care about others.

name: Sentret
text:
When acting as a lookout, it warns others of danger
by screeching and hitting the ground with its tail.

name: Hoothoot
ability: [{"info": "Insomnia", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon can\u2019t be Asleep."}]
text:
It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so
fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

name: Stantler
text:
This Pokémon apparently used to live in much
harsher environments, and thus it once had
stronger psychic powers than it does now.

name: Blissey
text:
Anyone who takes even one taste of Blissey’s
egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant
to everyone.

name: Yanma
text:
Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its
head. It won’t miss prey—even those behind it.

name: Flareon
text:
Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated,
and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000
degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Misdreavus
text:
This Pokémon startles people in the middle of
the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

name: Mankey
text:
It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of
its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

name: Primeape
text:
It becomes wildly furious if it even senses
someone looking at it. It chases anyone
that meets its glare.

name: Nidoran♂
text:
The horn on a male Nidoran’s forehead contains
a powerful poison. This is a very cautious
Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

name: Nidorino
text:
With a horn that’s harder than diamond, this
Pokémon goes around shattering boulders as it
searches for a moon stone.

name: Nidoking
text:
When it goes on a rampage, it’s impossible to
control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it’s
lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.

name: Lickitung
text:
If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and
you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in.
The itch won’t go away, either.

name: Eevee
text:
Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to
adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Yanmega ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Leafeon ex
ability: [{"info": "Forest Breath", "effect": "Once during your turn, if this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot, you may take a Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Mismagius ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Lickilicky ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Oddish
text:
If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move.
It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

name: Gloom
text:
Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor.
The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance
of 1.25 miles.

name: Bellossom
text:
Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals
rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

name: Scyther
text:
It slashes through grass with its sharp
scythes, moving too fast for the human
eye to track.

name: Pinsir
text:
These Pokémon judge one another based on
pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make
for more popularity with the opposite gender.

name: Chikorita
text:
A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its
head. It is docile and loves to soak up sun rays.

name: Bayleef
text:
A spicy aroma emanates from around its neck.
The aroma acts as a stimulant to restore health.

name: Meganium
text:
The aroma that rises from its petals contains a
substance that calms aggressive feelings.

name: Ledyba
text:
These very cowardly Pokémon join together and
use Reflect to protect their nest.

name: Ledian
text:
It’s said that the patterns on its back are
related to the stars in the night sky, but the
details of that relationship remain unclear.

name: Sunkern
text:
It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning.
Knowing it’s weak, it simply feeds until it evolves.

name: Sunflora
text:
In the daytime, it rushes about in a hectic
manner, but it comes to a complete stop when
the sun sets.

name: Pineco
text:
It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it
from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

name: Shuckle ex
ability: [{"info": "Solid Shell", "effect": "This Pok\u00e9mon takes \u221220 damage from attacks."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Vulpix
text:
While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it
grows, several new tails are sprouted.

name: Ninetales
text:
It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails
is loaded with supernatural powers.

name: Cyndaquil
text:
It is timid and always curls itself up in a ball.
If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.

name: Quilava
text:
Before battle, it turns its back on its opponent to
demonstrate how ferociously its fire blazes.

name: Typhlosion
ability: [{"info": "Fire Breath", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may make your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon Burned."}]
text:
If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything
that touches it will instantly go up in flames.

name: Darumaka
text:
It derives its power from fire burning inside
its body. If the fire dwindles, this Pokémon will
immediately fall asleep.

name: Heatmor
text:
There’s a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in
the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the
hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.

name: Poliwag
text:
For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking.
The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of
the Pokémon’s innards showing through the skin.

name: Poliwhirl
text:
Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness.
This trait of Poliwhirl’s has been used in place of
lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

name: Politoed
ability: [{"info": "Lordly Cheering", "effect": "As long as this Pok\u00e9mon is on your Bench, attacks used by your Pok\u00e9mon that evolve from Poliwhirl do +40 damage to your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
At nightfall, these Pokémon appear on the shores
of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by
letting out cries that sound like shouting.

name: Horsea
text:
Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle
currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits
out pitch-black ink and escapes.

name: Seadra
text:
It’s the males that raise the offspring. While
Seadra are raising young, the spines on their
backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

name: Kingdra ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Magikarp
text:
An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may
jump high on rare occasions but never more
than seven feet.

name: Gyarados
text:
Once it appears, it goes on a rampage.
It remains enraged until it demolishes
everything around it.

name: Wooper
text:
This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the
water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

name: Quagsire
text:
It has an easygoing nature. It doesn’t care if it
bumps its head on boats and boulders
while swimming.

name: Qwilfish
text:
Be cautious if this Pokémon starts sucking in
water—it will soon attack by scattering the toxic
spikes that grow all over its body.

name: Corsola
text:
It will regrow any branches that break off its
head. People keep particularly beautiful Corsola
branches as charms to promote safe childbirth.

name: Remoraid
text:
The water they shoot from their mouths can hit
moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

name: Octillery
text:
Its instinct is to bury itself in holes. It often steals
the nesting holes of others to sleep in them.

name: Mantine
text:
While elegantly swimming in the sea, it ignores
Remoraid that cling to its fins seeking food scraps.

name: Suicune
text:
It races around the world to purify fouled water.
It dashes away with the north wind.

name: Corphish
text:
No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will
adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

name: Crawdaunt
ability: [{"info": "Unruly Claw", "effect": "Once during your turn, when you play this Pok\u00e9mon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pok\u00e9mon, you may discard a random Energy from your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws.
It is said to be extremely hard to raise.

name: Chinchou
text:
Its antennae, which evolved from a fin, have both
positive and negative charges flowing through them.

name: Lanturn ex
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Pichu
text:
It is unskilled at storing electric power.
Any kind of shock causes it to discharge
energy spontaneously.

name: Mareep
text:
If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece
doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

name: Flaaffy
text:
As a result of storing too much electricity,
it developed patches where even downy
wool won’t grow.

name: Ampharos
text:
The bright light on its tail can be seen far
away. It has been treasured since ancient
times as a beacon.

name: Elekid
text:
When a storm approaches, this Pokémon gets
restless. Once Elekid hears the sound of thunder,
it gets full-on rowdy.

name: Emolga
text:
As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles
with electricity. This Pokémon is cute, but it can
cause a lot of trouble.

name: Slowpoke
text:
It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five
seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

name: Slowking
text:
When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke’s
head and unlocked an extraordinary power.

name: Jynx
text:
Its strange cries sound like human language.
There are some musicians who compose songs
for Jynx to sing.

name: Cleffa
text:
According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen
in places where shooting stars have fallen.

name: Natu
text:
It is extremely good at climbing tree trunks and
likes to eat the new sprouts on the trees.

name: Xatu
text:
They say that it stays still and quiet because it is
seeing both the past and future at the same time.

name: Espeon ex
ability: [{"info": "Psychic Healing", "effect": "Once during your turn, if this Pok\u00e9mon is in the Active Spot, you may heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pok\u00e9mon."}]
rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

name: Unown
ability: [{"info": "POWER", "effect": "This Ability works if you have any Unown in play with an Ability other than POWER. Attacks used by your Pok\u00e9mon do +10 damage to your opponent\u2019s Active Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape
appears to have some meaning.

name: Wobbuffet
text:
It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its
body to pump up its counterstrike.

name: Snubbull
text:
It grows close to others easily and is also easily
spoiled. The disparity between its face and its
actions makes many young people wild about it.

name: Granbull
text:
While it has powerful jaws, it doesn’t care for
disputes, so it rarely has a chance to display
their might.

name: Sudowoodo
text:
Although it always pretends to be a tree,
its composition appears more similar to
rock than to vegetation.

name: Binacle
text:
After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they
adhere themselves to it and live together.
They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

name: Barbaracle
text:
Seven Binacle come together to form one
Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head
gives orders to those serving as the limbs.

name: Murkrow
text:
Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to
bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

name: Honchkrow
text:
It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never
forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.

name: Sneasel
text:
This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of
darkness, waiting to attack its prey.

name: Weavile
text:
Evolution made it even more devious.
It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.

name: Houndoom
text:
If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its
mouth, the pain will never go away.

name: Scizor
text:
This Pokémon’s pincers, which contain steel, can
crush any hard object they get ahold of into bits.

name: Mawile
text:
It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into
complacency, then bites with its huge,
relentless jaws.

name: Eevee
text:
Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to
adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Porygon
text:
State-of-the-art technology was used to create
Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokémon to be
created via computer programming.

name: Porygon2
ability: [{"info": "Buggy Evolution", "effect": "Whenever you attach an Energy from your Energy Zone to this Pok\u00e9mon, put a random card from your deck that evolves from this Pok\u00e9mon onto this Pok\u00e9mon to evolve it."}]
text:
This is a Porygon that was updated with special
data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about
many different subjects all on its own.

name: Porygon-Z
text:
Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to
move between dimensions, but the program also
caused instability in Porygon-Z’s behavior.

name: Ambipom
text:
It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both
of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze,
that’s proof it really likes you.

name: Dunsparce
text:
It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted,
it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.

name: Smeargle
text:
The fluid of Smeargle’s tail secretions changes
in the intensity of its hue as the Pokémon’s
emotions change.

text:
An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may
jump high on rare occasions but never more

name: Gyarados
text:
Once it appears, it goes on a rampage.
It remains enraged until it demolishes
everything around it.

name: Vaporeon
text:
It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with
a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

name: Magnemite
text:
The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units
at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which
allows it to float.

name: Magneton
ability: [{"info": "Volt Charge", "effect": "Once during your turn, you may take a Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic
force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

name: Jolteon
text:
It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted
by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

name: Nidoran♀
text:
Females are more sensitive to smells than males.
While foraging, they’ll use their whiskers to check
wind direction and stay downwind of predators.

name: Nidorina
text:
The horn on its head has atrophied. It’s thought
that this happens so Nidorina’s children won’t get
poked while their mother is feeding them.

name: Nidoqueen
text:
Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense.
With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield
its children from any kind of attack.

name: Sneasel
text:
This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of
darkness, waiting to attack its prey.

name: Pikachu
attack: [{"info": "{L} Gnaw 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
When it is angered, it immediately discharges the
energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Mewtwo
attack: [{"info": "{PPCC} Power Blast 120", "effect": "Discard 2 {P} Energy from this Pok\u00e9mon."}]
text:
It was created by a scientist after years of horrific
gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.

name: Chansey
attack: [{"info": "{CCC} Gentle Slap 60", "effect": ""}]
text:
This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs
and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

name: Meowth
attack: [{"info": "{C} Pay Day 10", "effect": "Draw 1 card."}]
text:
All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night,
it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

name: Bulbasaur
attack: [{"info": "{GC} Vine Whip 40", "effect": ""}]
text:
There is a plant seed on its back right from the
day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly
grows larger.

name: Magnemite
attack: [{"info": "{L} Lightning Ball 20", "effect": ""}]
text:
The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units
at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which
allows it to float.

name: Moltres ex
attack: [{"info": "{R} Inferno Dance", "effect": "Flip 3 coins. Take an amount of {R} Energy from your Energy Zone equal to the number of heads and attach it to your Benched {R} Pok\u00e9mon in any way you like."}, {"info": "{RCC} Heat Blast 70", "effect": ""}]
